import{_ as e,o,c as t,b as s}from"./app-de7a4551.js";const r={},a=s('<h1 id="monitor" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#monitor" aria-hidden="true">#</a> monitor</h1><p>A computer monitor is an electronic device used to display images and text on a computer screen. It is an essential component of a computer system, as it allows users to <code>interact</code> with software applications and access digital content. Monitors come in various sizes and types, including LCD, LED, OLED, and CRT monitors.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p>计算机显示器是一种用于在计算机屏幕上显示图像和文本的电子设备。它是计算机系统的重要组成部分，因为它允许用户与软件应用程序互动并访问数字内容。显示器有各种尺寸和类型，包括 LCD、 LED、 OLED 和 CRT 显示器。</p></details><details class="custom-container details"><summary>words</summary><p>interact ( interacting, interacted, interacts )<br><code>英 [ˌɪntərˈækt] 美 [ˌɪntərˈækt]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 相互交流，互动；相互作用，相互影响</p></blockquote></details><p>The <code>earliest</code> monitors were CRT (<code>Cathode</code> Ray <code>Tube</code>) monitors, which used cathode rays to project images onto a <code>phosphor</code> screen. These monitors were <code>bulky</code> and heavy, and their image quality was not as good as modern monitors. In the 1980s, VGA (Video <code>Graphics</code> Array) monitors became popular, offering higher <code>resolution</code> and better color <code>accuracy</code> than CRT monitors.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p>最早的显示器是 CRT (阴极射线管)显示器，它利用阴极射线将图像投射到荧光屏上。这些显示器又大又重，其图像质量不如现代显示器。在20世纪80年代，VGA (视频图形阵列)显示器变得流行起来，比 CRT 显示器提供更高的分辨率和更好的色彩准确度。</p></details><details class="custom-container details"><summary>words</summary><p>early ( earlier, earliest )<br><code>英 [ˈɜːli] 美 [ˈɜːrli]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 早期的，初期的；提早的，提前的；早开花的，早熟的<br> adv. 在早期，在初期；提早，提前</p></blockquote><p>cathode<br><code>英 [ˈkæθəʊd] 美 [ˈkæθoʊd]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 阴极；（电解池的）负极；（原电池的）正极</p></blockquote><p>tube<br><code>英 [tjuːb] 美 [tuːb]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 管；管子；道；电视<br> v. 把…装上管；把…弄成管状；使通过管子；〈英〉坐地下铁道车去</p></blockquote><p>phosphor<br><code>英 [ˈfɒsfə(r)] 美 [ˈfɑsfər]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 磷光体，磷光剂</p></blockquote><p>bulky ( bulkier, bulkiest )<br><code>英 [ˈbʌlki] 美 [ˈbʌlki]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 笨重的，庞大的；大块头的，高大肥胖的</p></blockquote><p>graphics<br><code>英 [ˈɡræfɪks] 美 [ˈɡræfɪks]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 图像；绘图；图样；图案</p></blockquote><p>resolution<br><code>英 [ˌrezəˈluːʃ(ə)n] 美 [ˌrezəˈluːʃ(ə)n]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 解决；分辨；解析；决议</p></blockquote><p>accuracy<br><code>英 [ˈækjərəsi] 美 [ˈækjərəsi]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 准确性，精确性；准确，精确</p></blockquote></details><p>In the 1990s, SVGA (Super Video Graphics Array) monitors <code>emerged</code>, providing even better image quality and color accuracy than VGA monitors. With the <code>advent</code> of LCD (Liquid <code>Crystal</code> Display) monitors in the early 2000s, computer monitors became <code>thinner</code>, lighter, and more <code>energy-efficient</code>. Today, high-resolution displays such as 4K and 8K monitors are available, offering even <code>sharper</code> and more detailed images.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p>在20世纪90年代，SVGA (高级视频图形阵列)显示器出现了，提供了比 VGA 显示器更好的图像质量和色彩准确性。随着21世纪初LCD(液晶显示器)的出现，电脑显示器变得更薄、更轻、更节能。如今，4K和8K显示器等高分辨率显示器应运而生，提供更加清晰和详细的图像。</p></details><details class="custom-container details"><summary>words</summary><p>emerge ( emerging, emerged, emerges )<br><code>英 [ɪˈmɜːdʒ]美 [ɪˈmɜːrdʒ]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 浮现，出现；显露，知悉；恢复过来，幸存下来；形成，兴起</p></blockquote><p>advent<br><code>英 [ˈædvent]美 [ˈædvent]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 出现，到来，问世；基督降临节（Advent）；基督降临，基督复临（Advent）</p></blockquote><p>crystal<br><code>英 [ˈkrɪst(ə)l] 美 [ˈkrɪst(ə)l]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 结晶，晶体；水晶；水晶玻璃；（钟表的）石英玻璃保护面，表蒙子<br> adj. 晶莹的，清澈透明的</p></blockquote><p>thin ( thinning, thinned, thinner, thins, thinnest )<br><code>英 [θɪn] 美 [θɪn]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 薄的；细的；瘦的；稀少的<br> v. 使变淡；变稀疏；变稀少；（使）变稀薄<br> adv. 薄薄地<br> n. 细小部分</p></blockquote><p>energy-efficient (also energy efficient)</p><blockquote><p>adj. 节能的，节约能源的；高能效的</p></blockquote><p>sharp ( sharper, sharpest, sharps ) <code>英 [ʃɑːp] 美 [ʃɑːrp]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 锋利的；尖的；（沙子，沙砾）由尖颗粒组成的；急转弯的；急剧的，骤然的（变化）；清晰的，鲜明的；剧烈的，强烈的；（语言）尖锐的，尖刻的；刺耳的；聪明的，敏锐的；（味道）浓烈的，辛辣的；吸引人的，时髦的；（风或霜）刺骨的；狡诈的；升半音的；音调偏高的<br> adv. 正点，准时；急转向地；音调偏高地；突然地，急剧地<br> n. （音符的）升半音；升半音号（#）；缝衣长针；锐利的东西（如针、注射器等）（sharps）；&lt;非正式&gt;骗子<br> v. &lt;美&gt;升音演奏；&lt;古&gt;（尤指牌戏中）欺骗</p></blockquote></details><p>Modern computer monitors also offer advanced features such as touch screens, multiple input options (e.g. HDMI, DisplayPort), and built-in speakers. They are also designed to be more environmentally friendly, with energy-saving modes and lower power <code>consumption</code> compared to CRT monitors.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p>现代计算机显示器还提供高级功能，如触摸屏、多种输入选项(如 HDMI、 DisplayPort)和内置扬声器。它们的设计也更加环保，与CRT显示器相比，它们具有节能模式和更低的功耗。</p></details><details class="custom-container details"><summary>words</summary><p>consumption<br><code>英 [kənˈsʌmpʃ(ə)n] 美 [kənˈsʌmpʃ(ə)n]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 消费，消耗；食用，引用，吸入；专用；&lt;旧&gt;肺痨，肺结核</p></blockquote></details><p>Overall, computer monitors play a crucial role in our daily lives, enabling us to work, play, and communicate with others in a more <code>immersive</code> way. As technology continues to advance, we can <code>expect</code> even more exciting developments in the future of computer monitors.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p>总体而言，计算机显示器在我们的日常生活中扮演着至关重要的角色，使我们能够以一种更加身临其境的方式工作、玩耍和与他人交流。随着技术的不断进步，我们可以期待未来计算机显示器的发展会更加令人兴奋。</p></details><details class="custom-container details"><summary>words</summary><p>immersive<br><code>英 [ɪˈmɜːsɪv] 美 [ɪˈmɜːrsɪv]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. （计算机系统或图像）沉浸式虚拟现实的</p></blockquote><p>expect ( expecting, expected, expects )<br><code>英 [ɪkˈspekt]美 [ɪkˈspekt]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 期待；预计；要求，指望；认为；怀孕</p></blockquote></details>',16),c=[a];function n(i,d){return o(),t("div",null,c)}const p=e(r,[["render",n],["__file","31-monitor.html.vue"]]);export{p as default};
